This paper investigates the correlation between code complexity and bugs, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions cyclomatic complexity and NPATH complexity, which are metrics commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL). The study involves analyzing real-world bugs, which falls under software development (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the usefulness of the results for building bug prediction models, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR) or machine learning (cs.LG).
